            </a>
        </div>
    
    <div class="story-card__description">
                
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/flint-michigan-water-crisis-ten-years-after">
                                    Ten Years After the Flint Water Crisis, Distrust and Anger Linger
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            A city is forever changed, and so is residents’ relationship with their water. The betrayal of trust by the institutions meant to protect Flint’s residents has made some of them extra cautious as they look to keep themselves and their community safe.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/anna-clark">Anna Clark</a> and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/sarahbeth-maney">Sarahbeth Maney</a>, Photography by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/sarahbeth-maney">Sarahbeth Maney</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-05-04EDT05:00">May 4, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
        </p>

            </div>
